===Etymology 1===
{{etyl|enm}} {{term|sake|sake|sake, cause|lang=enm}}, from {{etyl|ang}} {{term|sacu|sacu|cause, lawsuit, legal action, complaint, issue, dispute|lang=ang}}, from {{etyl|gem-pro|en}} {{recons|sakō||affair, thing, charge, accusation, matter|lang=gem-pro}}, from {{etyl|ine-pro|en}} {{recons|sag-||to investigate|lang=ine-pro}}. Akin to {{etyl|ofs|-}} {{term|seke|seke|dispute, strife, thing, matter|lang=ofs}} ({{etyl|nl|-}} {{term|zaak|zaak||lang=nl}} "cause, thing"), {{etyl|goh|-}} {{term|sahha|sahha|quarrel, dispute, thing|lang=goh}} ({{etyl|de|-}} {{term|Sache|Sache||lang=de}} "thing, legal cause"), {{etyl|non|-}} {{term|sök|sök|lawsuit|lang=non}}, {{term|sekja|sekja|dispute|lang=non}} ({{etyl|da|-}} {{term|sag|sag||lang=da}}, {{etyl|sv|-}} {{term|sak|sak||lang=sv}}), {{etyl|got|-}} {{term|𐍃𐌰𐌺𐌾𐍉|sc=Goth|tr=sakjo|lang=got||dispute, argument}}, {{etyl|ang|-}} {{term|socn|sōcn|inquiry, prosecution|lang=ang}}, {{etyl|ang|-}} {{term|secan|sēcan|to seek|lang=ang}}. More at [[soke]], [[soken]], [[seek]].

