=====Usage notes=====

* The word ''sake'' is generally used in constructions of the form "for X's sake" or "for the sake of X", where X is a noun. (See quotations.) 

*Garner's ''Modern American Usage'' notes it is common to write an apostrophe rather than apostrophe–ess in this construction when the noun ends in an /s/ or /z/ sound:  ''for appearance' sake''.

